ailed runs don't block subsequent attempts\n\nA typical cron entry might look like:\n```bash\n*/7 * * * * /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/utr-monitor >> /hom…","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"bbd387f6-e6c5-4d5b-b75d-e3b0827fe2ed","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:bbd387f6-e6c5-4d5b-b75d-e3b0827fe2ed","runAtMs":1778641200034,"durationMs":289315,"nextRunAtMs":1778643000000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":131691,"output_tokens":5914,"total_tokens":18399}}
