{"ts":1778675949480,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've executed the Ubiquiti Travel Router availability check script. Here's what happened:\n\n## Summary of the check\n\n**1. Page fetch**: Successfully downloaded the product page (315KB file saved to `/tmp/utr_page.html`)\n\n**2. Availability check**: \n- Found \"Sold Out\" in the page (1 occurrence)\n- Did not find \"Add to Cart\" in the page\n\n**3. Status determination**: Product is currently **SOLD OUT**\n\n**4. Status comparison**: \n- Last known status (from state file): `sold_out` (checked at 2026-05-13T11:30:00Z)\n- Current status: `sold_out`\n- **No change in status**\n\n**5. Telegram alert**: Not sent (status unchanged, no alert required)\n\n**6. State file updated**: \n- Updated `last_checked` timestamp to `2026-05-13T12:35:42Z`\n- Status remains `sold_out`\n\n## Script execution details\n\nThe cron job script works by:\n1. Fetching the Ubiquiti store page for the Travel Router\n2. Checking for \"Sold Out\" or \"Add to Cart\" strings\n3. Comparing current availability with last known status\n4. Sending a Telegram alert only if status changes\n5. Updating the state file with new timestamp\n\nSince the product remains sold out (same as the last check), no alert was triggered. The script would have sent a Telegram message if the product became available.\n\n## Cleanup\n\nI've cleaned up the temporary file `/tmp/utr_page.html` and the state file has been updated with the latest check timestamp.\n\nThe monitoring system is working correctly - it detected the product is still sold out and updated the check timestamp without sending unnecessary alerts.","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"5ae699b7-78e6-4f62-a85a-5c3e78190075","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:5ae699b7-78e6-4f62-a85a-