{"ts":1778680905623,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I can see you've shared the cron job script for monitoring Ubiquiti Travel Router availability. Looking at your workspace, you already have a complete monitoring system implemented with:\n\n1. **Main monitoring script**: `check_utr_availability.sh` - A well-written bash script that matches your description\n2. **State tracking**: `utr_state.json` shows last status was \"sold_out\" on May 13, 2026 at 13:32:39Z\n3. **Configuration**: `utr-monitor.env` with Telegram token and chat ID configured\n4. **Supporting files**: Setup scripts, test scripts, and documentation\n\nThe implementation looks thorough with error handling, retries, Telegram alerts, and proper state management.\n\nSince you shared the script but didn't ask for anything specific, I'm wondering if you'd like me to:\n\n1. **Test the current implementation** - Run the script to verify it works\n2. **Check if a cron job is set up** - See if it's running automatically\n3. **Verify the Telegram alerts** - Test the notification functionality\n4. **Review the implementation** - Confirm it matches your requirements\n\nWould you like me to proceed with any of these, or is there something specific you need help with regarding the UTR monitoring system?","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"99f43e2c-b62e-4688-92e6-ea3b6dab0be1","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:99f43e2c-b62e-4688-92e6-ea3b6dab0be1","runAtMs":1778680800028,"durationMs":105584,"nextRunAtMs":1778682600000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":118009,"output_tokens":2570,"total_tokens":21942}}
{"ts":1778682768427,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I checked the current Ubiquiti Travel Router availability. Here's what I found:\n\n**Current Status:** Sold Out\n**Last Check in State File:** Sold Out (2026-05-13T13:32:39Z)\n**Status Change:** No change - still sold out\n\nThe page contains \"Sold Out\" text (found in the HTML), and there's no \"Add to Cart\" text visible. According to your script's logic, this means the product is currently sold out, and since the status hasn't changed from the last check, the script would just update the timestamp in the state file and exit silently.\n\n**Script Analysis:**\n- The curl command works correctly and fetches the page\n- The string detection logic (\"Sold Out\" vs \"Add to Cart\") appears sound\n- The state file exists and contains valid JSON\n- The comparison logic would correctly identify no status change\n\n**Potential Issues I Noticed:**\n1. **Missing state file handling:** If `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/utr_state.json` doesn't exist (first run), the `cat` command would fail. The script doesn't handle this case.\n2. **Dependency on `jq`:** The script uses `jq` to parse JSON. If `jq` isn't installed, it would fail.\n3. **Telegram token:** The script references `TELEGRAM_TOKEN` env var but doesn't check if it's set before attempting to send alerts.\n\nWhat would you like me to do?\n- Test the full script execution (I can create a test version)\n- Fix the missing state file issue\n- Check if `jq` is installed\n- Set up the cron job properly\n- Something else?\n\nThe script looks mostly complete and functional - it just needs some error handling improvements.","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"45b5a71a-68c0-4166-a530-ed9577edd44c","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:45b5a71a-68c0-4166-