{"ts":1778713381374,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've successfully completed the Ubiquiti Travel Router availability check. Here's what I did:\n\n1. **Fetched the product page**: Downloaded the current product page from the Ubiquiti store using curl.\n\n2. **Checked availability status**: \n   - Found \"Sold Out\" in the page content\n   - Did not find \"Add to Cart\" in the page content\n   - This confirms the product is currently SOLD OUT\n\n3. **Checked previous state**: Read the existing state file which showed:\n   - Last status: \"sold_out\" (from 30 minutes ago at 22:30 UTC)\n   - Last checked: 2026-05-13T22:30:00Z\n\n4. **Compared status**: The current status (sold_out) matches the previous status (sold_out), so there's no change in availability.\n\n5. **Updated state file**: Since the status hasn't changed, I updated only the timestamp to the current time (23:00 UTC) while keeping the status as \"sold_out\".\n\n**Result**: The Ubiquiti Travel Router remains sold out. No Telegram alert was sent because the status hasn't changed from the previous check. The state file has been updated with the new timestamp for the next scheduled check.\n\nThe cron job has completed successfully and exited silently as instructed when there's no status change.","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"cf30ef63-1ef8-4460-b5b0-ae11c0f11c11","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:cf30ef63-1ef8-4460-b5b0-ae11c0f11c11","runAtMs":1778713200055,"durationMs":181284,"nextRunAtMs":1778715000000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":352269,"output_tokens":2351,"total_tokens":71496}}
