{"ts":1778749362398,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've successfully completed the Ubiquiti Travel Router availability check. Let me review what I did:\n\n1. **Fetched the product page**: Used `curl` to download the Ubiquiti Travel Router product page to `/tmp/utr_page.html`\n\n2. **Checked for availability strings**: \n   - Found \"Sold Out\" multiple times in the HTML (specifically in `<div class=\"sc-1x3sjmh-0 cfWhQA\"> Sold Out</div>`)\n   - Did not find \"Add to Cart\" anywhere in the page\n\n3. **Determined current status**: Based on finding \"Sold Out\" and not finding \"Add to Cart\", the product is **SOLD OUT**\n\n4. **Compared with previous state**: \n   - Previous status (from state file): \"sold_out\" \n   - Current status: \"sold_out\"\n   - **Status has NOT changed**\n\n5. **Updated state file**: Since the status didn't change, I updated only the timestamp in `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/utr_state.json` to reflect the current check time (2026-05-14T09:00:00Z)\n\n6. **No alert sent**: According to the instructions, when the status doesn't change, I should just update the timestamp and exit silently - no Telegram alert is needed.\n\nThe check is complete. The Ubiquiti Travel Router remains sold out, same as the last check 30 minutes ago. The state file has been updated with the new timestamp.","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"e7e08d52-24ac-4624-ab82-9b13a79b83a7","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:e7e08d52-24ac-4624-ab82-9b13a79b83a7","runAtMs":1778749200042,"durationMs":162338,"nextRunAtMs":1778751000000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":190620,"output_tokens":3839,"total_tokens":48824}}
{"ts":1778751188151,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've completed the Ubiquiti Travel Router availability check. Here's what I did:\n\n1. **Fetched the product page**: Successfully downloaded the HTML from the Ubiquiti store using curl\n2. **Checked availability status**: Found \"Sold Out\" in the HTML content, confirming the product is currently unavailable\n3. **Read the existing state**: The state file showed the last status was also \"sold_out\" (last checked at 9:00 AM UTC)\n4. **Compared status**: The current status (\"sold_out\") matches the last known status (\"sold_out\") - no change\n5. **Updated the state file**: Since the status hasn't changed, I only updated the timestamp to the current time (9:30 AM UTC)\n\nThe cron job has completed successfully. No Telegram alert was sent because the availability status remains unchanged (still sold out). The state file has been updated with the new check timestamp.","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"5859eeb2-86cf-4569-b72c-6707355fdb01","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:5859eeb2-86cf-4569-b72c-6707355fdb01","runAtMs":1778751000165,"durationMs":187967,"nextRunAtMs":1778752800000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":161572,"output_tokens":2180,"total_tokens":47349}}
