{"ts":1778754859570,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've successfully executed the Ubiquiti Travel Router availability check as described in the cron job. Here's a complete summary of what was done:\n\n## Execution Summary\n\n**1. Page Fetch**: Downloaded the product page using `curl` to `/tmp/utr_page.html`\n\n**2. Availability Check**: \n- Searched for \"Sold Out\" - **FOUND** (multiple instances in the HTML)\n- Searched for \"Add to Cart\" - **NOT FOUND**\n- **Conclusion**: Product is SOLD OUT\n\n**3. Status Comparison**:\n- Previous status (from state file): `sold_out` (last checked: 2026-05-14T10:00:00Z)\n- Current status: `sold_out`\n- **Result**: Status unchanged\n\n**4. State Update**:\n- Updated `last_checked` timestamp to current time: `2026-05-14T10:30:00Z`\n- Maintained `last_status` as `sold_out`\n- File updated: `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/utr_state.json`\n\n**5. Alert Status**: No Telegram alert sent (status unchanged, per instructions)\n\n## Key Findings\n\nThe Ubiquiti Travel Router (UTR) remains out of stock. The monitoring script worked correctly:\n- Successfully fetched the product page\n- Correctly identified the \"Sold Out\" status\n- Properly compared with previous state\n- Updated the timestamp without sending unnecessary alerts\n\nThe cron job logic is sound - it only sends alerts when the availability status actually changes (from available to sold out or vice versa), which helps avoid notification spam while still monitoring for stock changes.","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"7e4f7def-0a67-4299-a5db-e191c32df13e","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:7e4f7def-0a67-4299-a5db-e191c32df13e","runAtMs":1778754600046,"durationMs":259505,"nextRunAtMs":1778756400000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"