{"ts":1778860941727,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've successfully completed the Ubiquiti Travel Router availability check as requested in the cron job instructions. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary of the Availability Check\n\n**1. Fetched the product page:**\n- Used `curl` to download the Ubiquiti Travel Router product page to `/tmp/utr_page.html`\n\n**2. Analyzed availability status:**\n- Found \"Sold Out\" text in the HTML content\n- Did not find \"Add to Cart\" text\n- Conclusion: Product is **SOLD OUT**\n\n**3. Checked previous state:**\n- Read existing state file at `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/utr_state.json`\n- Previous status: `\"sold_out\"` (last checked: 2026-05-15T15:32:37+00:00)\n\n**4. Compared status:**\n- Current status: `\"sold_out\"`\n- Previous status: `\"sold_out\"`\n- **No change in status**\n\n**5. Updated state file:**\n- Since status didn't change, only updated the timestamp\n- New timestamp: 2026-05-15T16:00:00+00:00 (as provided in the instructions)\n- No Telegram alert was sent (only sent on status changes)\n\n**6. Final state:**\n```json\n{\n  \"last_status\": \"sold_out\",\n  \"last_checked\": \"2026-05-15T16:00:00+00:00\"\n}\n```\n\nThe cron job has been executed successfully according to the specified workflow. The product remains sold out, so no notification was necessary. The system will continue monitoring and will send an alert only when the status changes from sold out to available or vice versa.","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"b515b307-8abb-42df-9081-0196f40e1f94","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:b515b307-8abb-42df-9081-0196f40e1f94","runAtMs":1778860800039,"durationMs":141676,"nextRunAtMs":1778862600000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":208927