{"ts":1778904135296,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've successfully executed the Ubiquiti Travel Router availability check as specified in the cron job. Here's what I did:\n\n1. **Fetched the product page**: Used `curl` to download the Ubiquiti Travel Router product page HTML to `/tmp/utr_page.html`\n\n2. **Checked availability status**: \n   - Found \"Sold Out\" in the HTML (specifically: `<div class=\"sc-1x3sjmh-0 cfWhQA\"> Sold Out</div>`)\n   - Did not find \"Add to Cart\" in the HTML\n   - According to the cron job logic, this means the product is **SOLD OUT**\n\n3. **Read current state**: The state file `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/utr_state.json` existed and showed:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"last_status\": \"sold_out\",\n     \"last_checked\": \"2026-05-16T03:30:00+00:00\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Compared status**: The current status (\"sold_out\") matches the last known status (\"sold_out\") - no change\n\n5. **Updated state file**: Since the status hasn't changed, I only updated the timestamp to the current time (2026-05-16T04:00:00+00:00) as instructed\n\n6. **No alert sent**: Because the status didn't change (available → sold out or sold out → available), no Telegram alert was needed\n\nThe cron job has completed successfully. The Ubiquiti Travel Router remains sold out, and the state file has been updated with the latest check timestamp.","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"d1b6c9ce-8de2-43d7-a9b9-69788c47954a","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:d1b6c9ce-8de2-43d7-a9b9-69788c47954a","runAtMs":1778904000030,"durationMs":135258,"nextRunAtMs":1778905800000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":209737,"output_tokens":2669,"total_tokens":47709}}
