{"ts":1778913208511,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've completed the Ubiquiti Travel Router availability check. Let me walk through my reasoning and the execution details.\n\n## What I Did\n\n1. **Read the existing state**: Found the product was last checked at 05:33 UTC and was marked as \"sold_out\"\n2. **Fetched the current product page**: Used curl to download the UTR product page to /tmp/utr_page.html\n3. **Checked for availability indicators**: Searched for \"Sold Out\" (case-insensitive) in the HTML and found it present\n4. **Determined current status**: Since \"Sold Out\" was found, the product is currently sold out\n5. **Compared with previous status**: Both current and previous status are \"sold_out\" - no change\n6. **Updated the state file**: Updated the timestamp to the current time (06:30 UTC) while keeping status as \"sold_out\"\n\n## Key Considerations\n\n**String Matching Approach**: I used `grep -i \"sold out\"` which performs case-insensitive matching. This is robust against minor HTML formatting variations. The page clearly contains \"Sold Out\" text in multiple locations, including a disabled \"Sold Out\" button and status indicators in the JSON data.\n\n**\"Add to Cart\" Check**: While I didn't run an explicit `grep -i \"add to cart\"`, the HTML output I examined showed no \"Add to Cart\" buttons or text. The product interface shows a disabled \"Sold Out\" button instead.\n\n**Edge Cases Handled**:\n- **Curl success**: Verified with `&& echo \"Page fetched successfully\"`\n- **State file existence**: The file existed, so I read and updated it\n- **Timestamp format**: Used ISO 8601 format as specified\n- **No status change**: Properly skipped Telegram alert as instructed\n\n**What If Neither String Was Found?**: The instructions say to wait 5 minutes and retry. Since this was a one-time execution (not a looping cron job), I executed once. If this were an actual cron job running periodically, it would retry on the next scheduled run.\n\n## Potential Improvements for Future Runs\n\n1. **Explicit dual-check**: Run both `grep -i \"sold out\"` and `grep…","delivered":false,"deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"eb514ca7-0ca9-4d6c-b76d-e057de5182e9","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:eb514ca7-0ca9-4d6c-b76d-e057de5182e9","runAtMs":1778913000050,"durationMs":208441,"nextRunAtMs":1778914800000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":177882,"output_tokens":5134,"total_tokens":48782}}
