{"ts":1778951314910,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've successfully set up your Ubiquiti Travel Router availability monitoring system. Here's what's now in place:\n\n## ✅ Current Status\n- **Monitor script**: `utr-availability-monitor.sh` - fully implements all your requirements\n- **Scheduler**: `utr-scheduler.sh` - runs the monitor every 15 minutes (900 seconds)\n- **Environment**: `utr-monitor.env` - contains Telegram credentials\n- **State tracking**: `utr_state.json` - tracks last status and timestamp\n- **Logs**: `utr-monitor.log` and `utr-scheduler.log` - record all activity\n\n## 🚀 System is Now Running\nThe scheduler is running in the background and will:\n1. Check availability every 15 minutes\n2. Send Telegram alerts when status changes (available ↔ sold_out)\n3. Update the state file with each check\n4. Retry if the page fetch fails (waits 5 minutes and tries again)\n\n## 📊 Current State\n```json\n{\n  \"last_status\": \"sold_out\",\n  \"last_checked\": \"2026-05-16T17:07:29Z\"\n}\n```\n\n## 🔧 How It Works\n1. **Every 15 minutes**: Scheduler runs `utr-availability-monitor.sh`\n2. **Page check**: Fetches https://store.ui.com/us/en/category/wifi-special-devices/products/utr\n3. **Status detection**: \n   - \"Sold Out\" → `sold_out`\n   - \"Add to Cart\" → `available`\n4. **Alert logic**: Sends Telegram message only when status changes\n5. **State persistence**: Updates `utr_state.json` after each check\n\n## 📱 Telegram Alerts\n- **Available**: \"🚨 *Ubiquiti Travel Router is AVAILABLE!* Check it out: [link]\"\n- **Sold Out**: \"❌ Ubiquiti Travel Router is now SOLD OUT\"\n- Sent to chat ID: 8623402151\n\n## 📝 Logs\n- `utr-scheduler.log`: Scheduler startup and loop timing\n- `utr-monitor.log`: Detailed check results and status changes\n\n## 🛠️ Manual Testing\nYou can test the system anytime with:\n```bash\nexport TELEGRAM_TOKEN=\"8629480213:AAGoHm6UXRhgfmo-UdIt6Kcdpzi1dE8HU5I\"\nexport TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=\"8623402151\"\n./utr-availability-monitor.sh\n```\n\n## ⚠️ Note on Cron\nThe system doesn't have traditional cron available, but the scheduler script (`utr-scheduler.sh`)…","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"dcb2e537-0014-44be-96d8-ed8d8db25cec","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:dcb2e537-0014-44be-96d8-ed8d8db25cec","runAtMs":1778950800043,"durationMs":514853,"nextRunAtMs":1778952600000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":568890,"output_tokens":13166,"total_tokens":30413}}
