{"ts":1779293099507,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I can see your Ubiquiti Travel Router monitoring system is fully implemented and working correctly. Here's what I found:\n\n## Current Status\n- **Product Status:** Sold Out (confirmed at 16:02:23 UTC)\n- **Last Check:** 2026-05-20T16:02:23Z\n- **Previous Status:** Sold Out (no change)\n- **Telegram Token:** Configured ✓\n- **Monitoring Script:** Working correctly ✓\n\n## System Configuration\nYou have a complete monitoring system with:\n1. **Main monitor script** (`utr_availability_monitor.sh`) - Checks availability and sends alerts\n2. **Daemon script** (`utr_daemon.sh`) - Runs checks every 15 minutes in the background\n3. **Cron wrapper** (`cron-utr-monitor.sh`) - For cron-based scheduling\n4. **State tracking** (`utr_state.json`) - Stores last known status\n5. **Environment configuration** (`utr-monitor.env`) - Contains Telegram token\n\n## Current Issue\nThe system is **not running automatically**. Neither cron jobs nor the daemon are currently active. The daemon PID file exists but the process isn't running.\n\n## Options\n1. **Start the daemon** - Runs checks every 15 minutes in the background\n2. **Set up a cron job** - More traditional scheduling approach\n3. **Manual checks only** - Run the script manually when you want to check\n\nWould you like me to start the monitoring daemon so it runs automatically every 15 minutes?","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"b34a89b9-1588-49c9-bdbe-2995d6db7b49","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:b34a89b9-1588-49c9-bdbe-2995d6db7b49","runAtMs":1779292800024,"durationMs":299470,"nextRunAtMs":1779294600000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":534969,"output_tokens":5647,"total_tokens":53619}}
