{"ts":1779467599983,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I can see you have a complete Ubiquiti Travel Router availability monitoring system already implemented. The cron job specification you shared matches exactly what's in your `utr-availability-monitor.sh` script.\n\n## Current Status\n\nThe system is working correctly:\n- **Last check**: May 22, 2026 at 16:32:55Z\n- **Current status**: SOLD OUT\n- **Previous status**: SOLD OUT (unchanged since last check)\n- **Telegram alerts**: Configured but not triggered (status unchanged)\n\n## System Components\n\nYour monitoring system includes:\n\n1. **Main monitor script** (`utr-availability-monitor.sh`) - Exactly matches your cron specification\n2. **Cron wrapper** (`cron-utr-monitor.sh`) - Loads environment variables and runs the monitor\n3. **Environment config** (`utr-monitor.env`) - Contains Telegram token and chat ID\n4. **State tracking** (`utr_state.json`) - Tracks last known status and timestamp\n5. **Logging** (`utr-monitor.log`) - Records all check activities\n\n## Verification\n\nI ran a manual test and confirmed:\n- The script successfully fetches the product page\n- Correctly identifies \"Sold Out\" status\n- Updates the state file with current timestamp\n- No Telegram alert sent (status unchanged)\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Cron scheduling**: The system appears to be running manually or via another scheduler. You might want to set up a regular cron job (e.g., every 15-30 minutes) if not already done.\n\n2. **Log rotation**: Consider adding log rotation for `utr-monitor.log` to prevent it from growing too large.\n\n3. **Error handling**: The script already has good error handling with retry logic for failed curl requests.\n\n4. **Testing alerts**: You could temporarily modify the state file to test Telegram alerts work when status changes.\n\nThe system is ready to alert you immediately when the Ubiquiti Travel Router becomes available again.","deli