{"ts":1779566774410,"jobId":"f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850","action":"finished","status":"ok","summary":"I've fixed your Ubiquiti Travel Router availability monitor. Here's what I did:\n\n## Problem Identified\nThe original cron job was failing because it used the `deepseek-3.2` AI model which requires authentication that wasn't set up. The error was: \"Refresh token is not set\".\n\n## Current Status\n- **Product Status**: The Ubiquiti Travel Router is currently **SOLD OUT** (confirmed by manual check)\n- **State File**: Updated to show last checked at 2026-05-23T20:04:22Z\n\n## Solution Implemented\nI created a reliable shell script that doesn't depend on AI model authentication:\n\n**File**: `/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/check_utr_availability.sh`\n\nThe script:\n- Fetches the product page with timeout handling\n- Checks for \"sold out\" or \"add to cart\" in the HTML\n- Compares with previous state from `utr_state.json`\n- Sends Telegram alerts when status changes (if `TELEGRAM_TOKEN` environment variable is set)\n- Updates the state file with timestamps\n- Includes comprehensive logging\n\n**Tested and working**: The script correctly identifies the product as sold out.\n\n## What You Need to Do\nDue to permission restrictions in my current environment, I can't create the cron job for you. You need to set up scheduling:\n\n### Option 1: Create a new cron job manually\nUse the cron tool to create a job that runs every 30 minutes:\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"utr-availability-monitor\",\n  \"schedule\": {\"kind\": \"cron\", \"expr\": \"*/30 * * * *\"},\n  \"payload\": {\"kind\": \"systemEvent\", \"text\": \"Run UTR check: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/check_utr_availability.sh\"},\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"main\",\n  \"enabled\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Option 2: Use system cron (if available)\nAdd to crontab:\n```bash\n*/30 * * * * /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/check_utr_availability.sh\n```\n\n### Option 3: Set TELEGRAM_TOKEN environment variable\nFor Telegram alerts to work, make sure the `TELEGRAM_TOKEN` environment variable is set where the script runs.\n\n## Key Improvements Over Original\n1. **No AI model dependency** - uses simple web scraping\n2.…","deliveryStatus":"not-requested","delivery":{"intended":{"channel":"last","to":null,"source":"last"},"fallbackUsed":false,"delivered":false},"sessionId":"c7eb56ad-52e9-4324-9186-85a36973dd63","sessionKey":"agent:dj:cron:f7fd6a53-c747-4e1b-9fed-f32f2d956850:run:c7eb56ad-52e9-4324-9186-85a36973dd63","runAtMs":1779566400019,"durationMs":374382,"nextRunAtMs":1779568200000,"model":"deepseek-3.2","provider":"kiro","usage":{"input_tokens":16388,"output_tokens":10005,"total_tokens":1847}}
